					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I can assure you that newer TVs <strong>do</strong> interlace video when they are told to - in HDTV "1080i", the "i" stands for "interlaced". Also, I have personally connected my NES to an HDTV and was able to verify that it did <em>not</em> try to merge multiple frames together - when Mario got hit and shrunk, he flickered like he was supposed to.
<br />
<br />The only sets that seem to have trouble are LCD and Plasma TVs - CRTs can interlace just fine.</div>

					
